This article first appeared at southern weekend and is not to be reprinted without permission

By Tan Chang, southern weekend correspondent

Southern weekend intern, Lee pei-wan

Associate Editor | Henin Ho

On January 24,2020, the new pneumonia prevention and Control Headquarters in Wuhan issued circular No. 7, which classified the diagnosis and screening of Febrile citizens in the city, with the primary diagnosis carried out by the community. Since then, more than 200 community health service centers in Wuhan have also been at the forefront of the epidemic.

A week later, southern weekly spoke with the heads of four community health centers to hear their stories. What they have done, what they have seen, and what they have thought, paint a picture of how the capillary system really works in this new outbreak of pneumonia.

1
"The conflict has intensified here. "

1

###"The conflict has intensified here. "

Qin Qi (not his real name) , director of a Community Health Service Center in Wuhan

As a community health service center at the grassroots level, we had virtually no capacity to respond to this epidemic. The sudden designation of our Community Hospital as triage unit by the HHS is a great test for us.

In the absence of protection, we immediately set up a triage desk, fever patients as long as we do not prevaricate, round the clock. From the morning of the first day of the Lunar New Year (January 25,2020) to yesterday afternoon (January 31,2020) , our workload has increased many times than usual, we do not feel tired, can do a duty for Wuhan, we are very proud.

But now... we are not sad because of the workload, we are often harassed by patients.

On the 30th, there was a story in the media that a community hospital would issue a referral for a suspected patient, and then dispatch a vehicle to a designated hospital. I immediately asked the Health Commission leadership, where there is a "referral sheet" this matter? I later reported the article because it didn't fit our current procedures and I didn't want my resident friend to be misled. Sure enough, as soon as the article was published, four patients came to our place the next day.

According to the procedure, we can only write "referral fever clinic" on the medical records, but we and designated hospitals are not docking. Fixed-point hospital is not enough, fever patient can not find bed, think community should be responsible, Neighborhood Committee officer and Community Health Service Center should send him to see a doctor. Their feelings we can understand, but now the conflict is indeed on our side, on our side intensified.

We actually have a strong sense of powerlessness every day. Fixed-point hospital bed is insufficient this outstanding problem, by our Community Hospital now, the neighborhood committee is paying for this.

This time, primary-level medical institutions played a big role. We calmed a lot of patients on the phone, triaged a lot of mild cases, instructed them to observe at home, not to fever clinic, reduce the risk of infection. But the later period problem can not solve, our earlier period work does again good also in vain.

Every time a new designated hospital came out, I tried to call, trying to help us in the hands of patients who can not stay in the hospital bed. But I couldn't get through on a public phone, so I had to try to find someone I knew. We want to help our patients, but it's just too much for us. The patient questioned us and said we were deliberately leaving the bed for our own people... we weren't afraid to do things, but we were afraid of being wronged. Maybe Vulcan Mountain, Thor Mountain Hospital has been built up, things will be much better.

I know many grassroots doctors are now very collapsed, some in order to save protective clothing, all day dare not eat, dare not drink. Because we have to visit, according to regulations, the last visit to the next house after the need to change the protective clothing, otherwise we become a mobile source of infection. But we don't have the resources to do that.

This outbreak is also a great test of our basic level of doctors and courage. The other day an old man in the neighborhood died at home. He was never diagnosed, but just in case, the neighborhood asked us to come in and dispose of the body. The chief of public health and I went over, sealed him up with sterilized cotton balls, wrapped him in sheets, and disinfected his room. This is the most professional thing we've ever done.

2
"In early January, 10,000 N95 masks were snapped up. "

2

###"In early January, 10,000 N95 masks were snapped up. "

Tam Wai, officer-in-charge, Ching Ling Street Community Health Centre, Hongshan District

We are the largest community health service center in Wuhan, with the qualifications of a level-two hospital, and over 300 employees. The registered permanent residents and the floating population in our jurisdiction add up to nearly 200,000. The floating population is large and the management is complicated. Because right at the intersection of the highway, sometimes a patient comes down the highway, he can't control you, it's just a community hospital, you have to see the disease, forcing us to improve medical capacity.

This time we started stockpiling supplies at the beginning of January. I am the Hubei Province Medical Image Professional Committee Vice-chairman, also serves as the third-level hospital image branch discipline leader, therefore I knew the news earlier than others. First of all, I had to support the canteen to snap up a batch of food, and then my brothers in the designated hospital told me that there are medical staff infection, I snapped up protective supplies. Like the N95 mask I prepared 10,000, a normal 7 dollars, I robbed the highest price is 20 dollars, and then can not buy. Because of this sensitivity, our protection is probably best in the community.

By the 10th of January, the Health Council in Wuhan began to assign us to do grid management. But at that time management is not tight, just let us do a fever patients registration, registration is over. The city did not order us as fever clinic, but our location is very special, there is no other two, three-level hospitals around a radius of seven kilometers, then we opened a respiratory disease clinic, for the treatment of ordinary fever patients.

To (January)23, fever patients on the instant increase, a day to see fever patients more than 100. We'll run lab tests, then CTS, and we'll start to see more and more of them.

New Year's Eve. All leave is cancelled on government orders. Some of US had already gone home, and we had to weed out pregnant, lactating lesbians, so we rounded up 270 people.

The busiest is the first day of the New Year. Because of the surge in fever cases in Wuhan, the government is expanding the number of designated hospitals for the new crown. There used to be some inpatients in those hospitals who had to be transferred out. We transferred more than 100 in-patients from two top-three hospitals, including patients who had just been transferred from the ICU after surgery, and 50 additional patients who were on intensive dialysis. So the medical pressure is very big, originally we will not accept (the condition) so serious patient. But we have also communicated with the third-tier hospitals, we can not do surgery or let their doctors come to do it.

From the first day to the third day, every day to the fever patients there are more than 100 people, the most day we gave 160 people a CT examination. The percentage of suspected cases where a CT showed changes in the lungs increased from 20% to 30% , and the highest was 50% on the third day of the eighth grade.

Suspected to be transferred to fever clinic and designated hospitals, but until the third day, this is very difficult. The beds haven't been expanded. They're all full. And suspicious cases must be ambulance, but the ambulance did not (idle) , we can only give them some medicine, let them go home to quarantine. It was one of the most chaotic days in Wuhan.

By the fourth day, things were better. There are three in Hongshan District, one of which is a hotel, to be handed over to the police, to us and to the streets. The day gave me half an hour to prepare people and supplies to receive this quarantine point, I divided the quarantine area and medical personnel, staff area, sent in 16 employees, three shifts. One night we herded suspected and feverish patients from the diaspora into isolation, one room each, and now there were nearly a hundred people in there. The government gives them food, we test them every morning, we give them antiviral drugs.

Now, we're not short of protective gear, but we're short of men. The isolation clothing should be changed every 4 hours, because of lack of manpower, or six or seven hours to change every time, drinking water, go to the toilet to endure. The medical staff was so stressed out that we moved the stereo to the cafeteria so they could listen to music while they ate.

3
"suspected cases of non-fever on the rise. "

3

###"suspected cases of non-fever on the rise. "

Hu Zhenbo, director of Xingou Qiao Street Community Health Service Center, Qingshan district

The Community Hospital floor, as a whole, is still short of protective equipment. We are a little better, before the Spring Festival procurement of a number of materials, but there are gaps, mainly lack of protective clothing. Later, we raised some protective clothing through the donation channel, but all did not meet the national standard.

There have been some changes in our triage patients in the past two days. Suspected cases of fever are decreasing, but suspected cases of non-fever are increasing. Patients with fevers are sent by the community. Patients without fevers come on their own. As a result, we tested some patients with no fever, and found that except for the fever, all the other three were consistent —— a low white count, a low lymphocyte, and ground glass lung. We need to look again to see if this is an individual problem in our hospital or a general problem in our community hospitals.

There is a big gap between different community hospitals in Wuhan. Our area of 50,000 people, the hospital hardware is not good, only more than 2,000 square meters of business room, but also relatively strong outpatient capacity, outpatient volume in the city is relatively large, such as today (January 31) outpatient to one hundred and forty. Suspicious reports, sometimes seven or eight a day, sometimes two or three.

In fact, since the 24th post, the number of outpatients coming to our center is actually less than some time ago. The main reason is through a variety of publicity, we know that non-special circumstances, emergency try not to come to the hospital. But the amount of work that we do in the home has increased, and we have to do in-home follow-up of close contacts every day, symptomatic observation of the symptoms, no symptoms of the main body temperature. Close contact data is sent down to the streets by the CDC, and the streets provide it to us.

The district home isolation treatment of patients with mild illness, we also need to track the daily home. In addition to routine tests for symptoms and body temperature, they should also be taught how to protect themselves at home and how to monitor themselves. Many people with mild illness are very scared, so we also need to give them psychological counseling. On the one hand, we should explain their condition clearly, and tell them that there are community hospitals and hospitals at all levels to provide them with medical care, reassure them not to be pessimistic.

Our public health team, which had been the main focus of the home invasion effort, was now overwhelmed by the redeployment of administrative staff and medical staff from other departments. Our doctors and nurses are still under a lot of stress about being infected. Overcoming this kind of pressure mainly depends on the training, lets everybody have the correct understanding to the disease. Then the members of the leading bodies and the Party members should demonstrate and go ahead without panic or fear. In fact, it is impossible to say that they are not afraid at all.

Many community hospitals are facing such pressure and challenges for the first time. Originally the foundation of the Community Hospital is relatively poor, medical graduates simply do not want to work in the Community Hospital, we recruit people are "eight immortals cross the sea each show magical powers. ". The inspiration for me from this outbreak is that we should strengthen the construction of community hospitals in normal times, so that we can keep our feet on the ground at critical moments.

4
"Hope Students return to school after the outbreak is over. "

4

###"Hope Students return to school after the outbreak is over. "

Kinko, director of the Wuhan University of Technology

We are a community health service center in a university, and 80% of our clients are students. With the students gone for the holidays, there are far fewer people coming to see us. Between our two campuses, we only see five or eight people with fever every day.

It is indeed a great relief for us that the students leave school during the winter vacation. If students are still on campus, they live in dormitories and attend classes together. The dining halls and toilets are all communal. The population density is high and the mobility is great. Once the epidemic is spread, it is difficult to control.

The school has informed the students that they are not allowed to go back to school without permission, and no accommodation will be arranged if they come back. Of course, it's impossible not to care if a student does return. The message: Don't come back. And Wuhan is closed, they can't come back.

Our supplies are still relatively adequate, mainly from alumni donations. I was at the alumni meeting the other day and found that alumni donations amounted to nearly two million RMB, including masks, protective clothing, alcohol, disinfectant, and thermometers. Let's just say we're well-armed.

If there is more, we will support other hospitals, but to be honest, we don't know how long the war will last, so we have to stock it up.

When school starts, it's up to the headquarters to decide. From a doctor's point of view, I certainly hope the epidemic is over and the students return to school.

(thanks to Guo Xiaoling, former secretary general of the Hubei Provincial Grassroots Health Association, for her help in this article.)
